    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Created by the priests of a Qadiran sect of Sarenites, the *sun wheels* were designed to protect the Dawnflower's followers in their quest to hunt down a dangerous cult trying to raise a spawn of the evil god Rovagug. Once they completed their crusade, these priests disbanded and went on to minister other congregations. They each took their *sun wheels* with them, handing them down to the next generations.  \n   \n This copper medallion is etched with a stylized sun, its rays shaped like the spokes of a wagon wheel. It tends to glint brightly when exposed to sunlight. While wearing this pendant, you gain a +1 item bonus to Religion checks. You must be good-aligned to use the sun wheel's true power: the following activation, which provides you a shield of burning force.",
        "level": 5,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "schema_version": 1.1,
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Abjuration",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
